      <div class="d-flex fd-column g3 p4 bg-green-100 bar-md">
        <h3 class="fs-h4 fw-bold fc-green-600">Do</h3>
        <ul class="list-unstyled fc-light-700 lh-relaxed">
          <li class="mb2">• Use semantic colors for their intended purpose</li>
          <li class="mb2">• Test color combinations for accessibility</li>
          <li class="mb2">• Use consistent color stops across your design</li>
          <li class="mb2">• Provide sufficient contrast for text</li>
          <li class="mb2">• Use hover and focus states for interactivity</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="d-flex fd-column g3 p4 bg-red-100 bar-md">
        <h3 class="fs-h4 fw-bold fc-red-600">Don't</h3>
        <ul class="list-unstyled fc-light-700 lh-relaxed">
          <li class="mb2">• Use red for non-error states</li>
          <li class="mb2">• Use low contrast color combinations</li>
          <li class="mb2">• Mix different color systems</li>
          <li class="mb2">• Use too many colors in one interface</li>
          <li class="mb2">• Ignore accessibility guidelines</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-light-025 p4 bar-md">
      <h3 class="fs-h4 fw-bold mb3">Color Accessibility Tips</h3>
      <ul class="list-unstyled fc-light-700 lh-relaxed">
        <li class="mb2">
          • <strong>Test contrast:</strong> Use tools like WebAIM's contrast checker
        </li>
        <li class="mb2">
          • <strong>Don't rely on color alone:</strong> Combine with icons, text, or patterns
        </li>
        <li class="mb2">
          • <strong>Consider colorblind users:</strong> Ensure information is accessible without
          color
        </li>
        <li class="mb2">
          • <strong>Use consistent patterns:</strong> Establish clear color meanings across your app
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

